      • crop

        public Texture crop​(int x,
                    int y,
                    int w,
                    int h)
        This function crops a texture image based on the given x, y, width, and height parameters.
        Parameters:
        x - The x-coordinate of the top-left corner of the rectangular area to be cropped from the original texture.
        y - The "y" parameter in the "crop" method is the vertical coordinate of the top-left corner of the rectangular area to be cropped from the original image.
        w - w stands for width. It is the width of the rectangular area that will be cropped from the original image.
        h - h stands for height. It is the height of the rectangular area that will be cropped from the original image.
        Returns:
        A Texture object is being returned.
